YesUsefulNo



                2
            

                By: FL409


                My experiences with First Niagara Bank have been stressful and unsatisfactory, on the whole, and I've actually been considering switching banks.I originally had an account through HSBC, and I'd never had a problem with them. However, HSBC shut down all of its bank branches in my part of the US, and there was an automatic switchover to First Niagara. I figured that hey, they're a more localized company. Why not give them a try?However, almost immediately, I had problems. About two weeks after the switchover, somebody put a debit card scanning device on the ATM inside my local First Niagara bank branch. They ended up getting the information for many different patrons of the branch, including myself. Though I was reimbursed quickly for the money taken out of my account by the perpetrators (over $700 total), the process was long and harrowing, and it seemed like they were accusing me of doing something wrong or irresponsible. But it was at their actual bank location that the skimming occurred! The whole reimbursement was not officially approved or resolved until months later. I should mention that the customer service of the bank tellers and managers at my actual branch location was amazing. They were very helpful, supportive and informative. However, they were previous employees of HSBC, so I can't give First Niagara credit for hiring them.Besides that whole fiasco, I've just found First Niagara to be a little shady or tight-lipped when it comes to added fees. For example, soon after the switchover, they implemented fees for not having enough money in your checking account, which HSBC had never done. Also, I recently received a bill of $15 for too many transactions in one month, but was never made aware that such fees existed.I'm still on the lookout for a new bank, and I caution anyone considering signing up with First Niagara. I'm sure many people have had positive experiences with them, and it is nice that they're regional, but I wish they were friendlier to willing customers and that they informed you more about their fees.… read more


